Project 5: Social Media Platform

Today's Focus: Large-scale Full Stack Application
What I Built: Feature-rich social media platform with:

Core Features:

User profiles with bio, photos, cover image

Post creation (text, images, videos)

Like, comment, share functionality

Real-time notifications

Friend system (follow/unfollow)

Direct messaging with WebSockets

News feed algorithm

Hashtag system

Advanced Features:

Live streaming with WebRTC

Stories (24-hour disappearing content)

Events creation and RSVP

Groups and communities

Marketplace for buying/selling

Job posting board

Analytics dashboard for page owners

Technical Implementation:
Microservices architecture

GraphQL API with Apollo Federation

Redis for caching and real-time features

Elasticsearch for search functionality

CDN for media delivery

WebSocket cluster for messaging

Queue system for background jobs

Monitoring with Prometheus and Grafana

Infrastructure:

Docker containers orchestrated with Kubernetes

CI/CD with GitLab CI

AWS deployment (EC2, RDS, S3, CloudFront)

Load balancing with NGINX

Database sharding for scalability


